    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1962-02-06T17:28:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1962-02-06T17:28:00-05:00" n="290"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d290">
                <head>290. Telegram From the <gloss type="from">Department of State</gloss> to the
                        <gloss type="to">Embassy in Laos</gloss>
                    <note n="0" type="source" xml:id="d290fn1">Source: Department of State, Central
                        Files, 751J.00/2–662. Secret; Niact. Drafted by <persName corresp="#p_CCT1"
                            >Cross</persName>, cleared by <persName corresp="#p_REE1"
                            >Rice</persName> and <persName corresp="#p_CH1">Cleveland</persName>,
                        and approved by <persName corresp="#p_HWA1">Harriman</persName>. Repeated
                        niact to London and to Bangkok and Paris.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                            when="1962-02-06T17:28:00-05:00">February 6, 1962, 5:28 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>703. Department has concluded that endeavors press <persName corresp="#p_PN1"
                        >Phoumi</persName> negotiate in good faith no longer hold promise success
                    and has therefore concluded time has come to direct negotiation with Souvanna.
                    However this can not take place while Nam Tha being attacked or in enemy
                    hands.</p>
                <p>You should therefore request <persName corresp="#p_AJM1">Addis</persName> that he
                    immediately go (Feb. seventh) to <persName corresp="#p_SPP1">Souvanna
                        Phouma</persName> with message from us to effect that when <persName
                        corresp="#p_SPP1">Souvanna Phouma</persName> calls off his attack on Nam Tha
                    (or if Nam Tha already <pb facs="0640" n="616" xml:id="pg_616"/> fallen he
                    withdraw from it) <gloss target="#t_USG1">USG</gloss> would be prepared to sit
                    down and negotiate with him directly on coalition government we could accept.
                    While we convinced <persName corresp="#p_PN1">Phoumi</persName> will not
                    negotiate in good faith and that we will be faced with one obstacle after
                    another which he will put up to avoid doing so, it clear we can not put strong
                    sanctions on <persName corresp="#p_PN1">Phoumi</persName> until <persName
                        corresp="#p_SPP1">Souvanna</persName> assures us he willing and able to
                    agree to government we can accept. Our intention is for you, <persName
                        corresp="#p_AJM1">Addis</persName> and <persName corresp="#p_FPL1"
                        >Falaize</persName> to negotiate directly with <persName corresp="#p_SPP1"
                        >Souvanna</persName> in Xieng Khouang and/or Luang Prabang as soon as
                    fighting stops.</p>
                <p>Wish reemphasize that mission by <persName corresp="#p_AJM1">Addis</persName>
                    should not hold up other negotiations for cease-fire. It obvious we can not
                    discuss coalition government with <persName corresp="#p_SPP1"
                        >Souvanna</persName> until attack on Nam Tha ceases.</p>
                <p>Foregoing discussed with British here. British will send separate message.<note
                        n="1" xml:id="d290fn2">Not found.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_RD1">
                            <hi rend="strong">Rusk</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
